cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

This paper deals with computer vision problems such as fine-grained sketch-based image retrieval and person re-identification, which are typically categorized under cs.CV. The paper proposes a framework for cross-domain instance matching, which involves learning representations that can be compared across different domains. This is a common problem in machine learning, which is often addressed using deep neural networks, falling under cs.LG and cs.AI. The paper also involves image and multimedia processing, which falls under cs.MM. Finally, the paper deals with information retrieval, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under cs.IR.
